<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 01:17:25 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>美国人尤其是年轻人对以色列和内塔尼亚胡的负面看法持续上升</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/negative-views-of-israel-netanyahu-continue-to-rise-among-americans-especially-young-people/</link><description>美国成年人对以色列和本杰明·内塔尼亚胡的看法变得更加负面，两党中 50 岁以下的大多数人对他们的评价都很差。</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 01:17:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/negative-views-of-israel-netanyahu-continue-to-rise-among-americans-especially-young-people/</guid></item><item><title>汽油价格是伊朗战争中美国人最关心的问题</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/07/gas-prices-are-americans-top-concern-in-iran-war/</link><description>69%的美国人担心伊朗战争导致天然气价格上涨，45%的人表示美国在避免平民伤亡方面做得不够。</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 01:02:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/07/gas-prices-are-americans-top-concern-in-iran-war/</guid></item><item><title>美国人从哪里获取健康信息以及他们信任什么？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/04/07/where-do-americans-get-health-information-and-what-do-they-trust/</link><description>医疗保健提供者是健康信息的重要来源。较小的份额从社交媒体和人工智能获取健康信息。</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 00:47:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/04/07/where-do-americans-get-health-information-and-what-do-they-trust/</guid></item><item><title>大约一半有兄弟姐妹的美国人至少与其中一个人关系密切</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/about-half-of-americans-with-siblings-are-close-to-at-least-one-of-them/</link><description>大约一半有兄弟姐妹的美国成年人与至少一个人非常或极其亲密，但亲密程度和支持程度因人口统计数据而异。</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 00:32:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/about-half-of-americans-with-siblings-are-close-to-at-least-one-of-them/</guid></item><item><title>共和党人不太可能说加入北约对美国有利</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/06/republicans-have-become-less-likely-to-say-nato-membership-benefits-the-us/</link><description>大约十分之四的共和党人 (38%) 表示，美国至少从加入北约中受益匪浅——低于去年的 49%。在民主党人中，82% 的人这么说。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Apr 2026 01:16:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/06/republicans-have-become-less-likely-to-say-nato-membership-benefits-the-us/</guid></item><item><title>美国人最大的税收挫败感：感觉一些富人、企业没有支付公平的份额</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/06/top-tax-frustrations-for-americans-feeling-that-some-wealthy-people-corporations-dont-pay-fair-share/</link><description>61% 的成年人表示，一些富人没有支付应得份额的感觉让他们很困扰。 60% 的人对某些公司有这样的看法。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Apr 2026 01:01:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/06/top-tax-frustrations-for-americans-feeling-that-some-wealthy-people-corporations-dont-pay-fair-share/</guid></item><item><title>美国人对能源问题看法的转变</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/04/03/americans-shifting-views-on-energy-issues/</link><description>过去六年里，认为国家应该优先考虑石油、煤炭和天然气而不是风能和太阳能的共和党人比例翻了一番，达到 71%。</description><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2026 01:09:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/04/03/americans-shifting-views-on-energy-issues/</guid></item><item><title>美国人如何看待特朗普处理贸易和关税的方式</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/01/how-americans-view-trumps-handling-of-trade-and-tariffs/</link><description>近十分之六的美国成年人不相信特朗普能够就贸易政策做出正确的决定。自 2025 年以来，美国与中国、加拿大和墨西哥之间的贸易观点发生了变化。</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 01:12:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/01/how-americans-view-trumps-handling-of-trade-and-tariffs/</guid></item><item><title>美国式的出生公民权在世界各地并不常见</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/us-style-birthright-citizenship-is-uncommon-around-the-world/</link><description>世界上还有 32 个国家/地区的出生权利公民身份法律与美国基本相似。另外 50 个左右的国家/地区的出生权利公民身份的变化更为有限。</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2026 01:22:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/us-style-birthright-citizenship-is-uncommon-around-the-world/</guid></item><item><title>2023 年，约 9% 的美国新生儿是未经授权或临时合法移民母亲出生的</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/about-9-of-us-births-in-2023-were-to-unauthorized-or-temporary-legal-immigrant-mothers/</link><description>一般来说，非法移民的出生趋势随着非法移民人口的增长和减少而变化。</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2026 01:07:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/about-9-of-us-births-in-2023-were-to-unauthorized-or-temporary-legal-immigrant-mothers/</guid></item></channel></rss>